  "notes": "Walloon (Walon), Gallo-Romance language spoken in Wallonia (Belgium) and parts of France. Official regional language of Wallonia. Digraph ch = /ʃ/, j = /ʒ/. Retains Latin w preserved as /w/. Closely related to Picard. Phonemic vowel length.",
